author: leeastley
title: Arsenal leave non-league Sutton changing room in a mess after their 2-0 FA Cup triumph
text:
There were bottles of drink and toilet roll left all over the floor of the humble changing room Getty Images 4 Arsenal did not leave the Sutton away dressing room in the state they found it in 
But Wenger seemed to enjoy the novelty of playing in surroundings unfamiliar to most of his multi-millionaire players. 
Wenger said: “The changing rooms for me were fantastic – the closer you are, the more united you are when you go out there.” Arsenal did not allow cameras into their dressing room like Sutton did related stories Class act Arsenal to donate £50,000 to help beaten FA Cup opponents Sutton build classrooms and fix the loos He Shaw is hungry Sutton back-up keeper Wayne Shaw gives fans a laugh as he munches a pie during second half Walk tall Sutton's Paul Doswell says 'it was a dream' to face Arsenal while Arsene Wenger admits minnows shocked him Gander Green invasion Sutton fans invade the pitch at Gander Green Lane after watching the biggest game in their club history against Arsenal 'class act' Theo Walcott signs Sutton players' shirts in dressing room after Arsenal's crushing FA Cup victory Five things we learnt Sutton 0 Arsenal 2: Theo Walcott scored his 100th goal to remind Arsene Wenger of scoring prowess
